                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310407-286-victim1964 t18310407-286-viclabel1517"></join> - we live in <placeName id="t18310407-286-crimeloc1518">Golden-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310407-286-crimeloc1518" type="placeName" value="Golden-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310407-286-crimeloc1518" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310407-286-off1515 t18310407-286-crimeloc1518"></join>. I had a bonnet in a cupboard in one of my rooms on the 21st of March - it was safe about eleven o'clock, and I missed it between eleven and twelve o'clock - this is it; I saw Elizabeth Bulmer with it in her hand last Monday week.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-286-person1966">
                  ELIZABETH 
                  BULMER
               <interp inst="t18310407-286-person1966" type="surname" value="BULMER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-286-person1966" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-286-person1966" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Milton-street, and am the wife of John Bulmer, a bricklayer. On the 21st of March I was in Chapel-street, and saw the prisoner there, between twelve and one o'clock - it is a good step from the prosecutor's; he asked me to buy a bonnet - I said I did not want one; he asked where I lived - I showed him over the way; he came to my house, and brought this bonnet - he asked me 4s. for it; I agreed to give him 3s. - I paid him 1s. 6d. then, and 1s. 6d. the next day; this is the bonnet - I gave it to the officer.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-286-person1967">
                  JOHN 
                  COHEN
               <interp inst="t18310407-286-person1967" type="surname" value="COHEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-286-person1967" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-286-person1967" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am Bulmer's brother-in-law. I saw this bargaining about the bonnet when I went home to dinner - the prisoner was sitting in a chair in my room, with it in his hand; and while I was eating my dinner, in came my sister, and bought it of him for 3s.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-286-person1968">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BALLARD
               <interp inst="t18310407-286-person1968" type="surname" value="BALLARD"></interp>
