                     <interp inst="t18310407-286-person1968" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-officer. I received the bonnet from Bulmer - she had it on her head, and the prosecutor claimed it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-286-person1969">
                  JOHN 
                  SMITH
               <interp inst="t18310407-286-person1969" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-286-person1969" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-286-person1969" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I took the prisoner, in Golden-lane, where his father keeps a shop - he mentioned the name of some person who he bought it of, but we could not find him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I met a young man I knew that day, and he asked me if I knew any lady who wanted to buy a bonnet - I sold it for him.</p>
